There is excitement in the air as Big Brother Naija season 7 holds a double launch on Saturday, July 23 and Sunday, July 24 at 7pm. Viewers will have the opportunity to watch the special unveil of the shw on DStv’s Africa Magic Showcase, Urban and Family channels. The show will also air on DStv channel 198 and GOtv channel 29, as well as on Showmax. Fans of the show will love this season because several pre-COVID-19 elements are returning to the game, such as the Ninjas and live studio audience. Also to be expected is a line-up of more engaging tasks, unpredictable twists and Big Brother’s wits. Organised by MultiChoice Nigeria and hosted by Ebuka Obi-Echendu, the Africa’s biggest reality show will kick off with the two-part launch before plunging into 72 days of what promises to be dramatic, insightful and downright entertaining. Sponsored by PiggyVest (formerly Abeg) and associate sponsored by Flutterwave, viewers should expect to experience talented youngsters, bellyaching laughs, emotional moments and candid advice from Ebuka throughout the season.